//
// SmolLM2-1.7B verify gate: top-k token-level inclusion check, NPU vs HF bf16,
// 2 prompts x 32 greedy tokens, k=5 (fast gate; `make verify-full` for the full
// sweep). Exercises the full production prefill + decode path through the verify
// subsystem (verify/verify_runner.py).
//
// NOT CI-triggered by design: the filename intentionally OMITS "peano", so the
// CI peano suite (`lit --filter "peano"`) does not collect it — keeping CI time
// bounded (llama32_1b's verify is the bf16 correctness signal in CI). Run on
// demand with:
//   lit -v programming_examples/llms/smollm2_1_7b/run_npu2_verify.lit
//
// No hf_token required: SmolLM2 uses the ungated HuggingFaceTB/SmolLM2-1.7B
// checkpoint (public, no gated download), unlike llama32_1b's meta-llama/*
// reference. So if this lit is ever promoted into CI, it needs only
// ryzen_ai_npu2 + peano — no secret.
//
// REQUIRES: ryzen_ai_npu2, peano
//
// RUN: mkdir -p test_peano_verify
// RUN: cd test_peano_verify
// RUN: make -f %S/Makefile clean
// RUN: make -f %S/Makefile verify PEANO_INSTALL_DIR=%PEANO_INSTALL_DIR | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: [verify] PASS
